      • hitGolFBall

        public void hitGolFBall(Integer power,
                        String direction)
                 throws GameOverException,
                        PowerExceedsMaxRangeException,
                        FileNotFoundException,
                        BallOutOfBoundsException,
                        UnsupportedEncodingException
        hit gold ball with power and to which direction on field. Ball will end on the block on field depending on the direction supplied, power and wind speed.
        For instance if
        ball is at [0,0];
        Wind speed is =[2,-2];
        Power = 5;
        Direction = RD;
        Final ball position after the shot will be [0+5+2, 0+5+(-2)] => [7,3]
        Wind [x,y]:
        x - positive means wind direction is right - R
        -x - negative means wind direction is left - L
        y - positive means wind direction is downwards - D
        -y - negative means wind direction is upwards - U
        Parameters:
        power - - Strength of your shot. Max power is 10.
        This is the number of blocks ball will travel when hit before
        considering wind resistance.
        direction - - Direction you want to hit the ball.
        You can hit ball in right, left, up and down direction and also diagonally.
        Options: Any one of R, RD, D, LD, L, LU, U, RU
        Throws:
        GameOverException - - When trying to hit the ball and ball is already in hole.
        PowerExceedsMaxRangeException - - Max power is 10
        BallOutOfBoundsException - - When ball lands outside field grid
        UnsupportedEncodingException
        FileNotFoundException
